# Sports jersey silhouettes (always)

When creating or editing **NBA / soccer / NFL** jersey templates or display art:

1. **Always show the jersey on a hanger** (Morocco / Spain photo style: hanger + dark locker/wood backdrop). Prefer a real photo back when available; otherwise the CSS hanger mount in `display-app.js` / `display.css`.
2. **Soccer** — slim short-sleeve shirt; fabric / kit fashion; name + number (name often arched); side accent panels OK. Match the presentation language of Morocco, Spain, Monaco photo backs.
3. **NBA** — sleeveless / tank cut; athleisure mesh feel; **big number**, name smaller/cleaner and higher on the back.
4. **NFL** — bulkier cut with yoke/shoulders; name **plate across the shoulders**; **huge number**; armor-adjacent, thicker graphics / heavier text shadow.
5. Do **not** ship flat diagonal stripe CSS as the only NBA/NFL/soccer identity — that reads as one generic jersey. Colors alone are not enough; silhouette + typography must differ by sport.
6. Keep `sport: "soccer" | "nba" | "nfl"` on catalog rows so `display-app.js` can pick `jersey-sport-*` classes.

Checklist before commit:

- [ ] Hanger presentation (photo or CSS mount)
- [ ] Correct sport silhouette class
- [ ] Sport-appropriate name/number hierarchy
- [ ] Previewed on `led-64x32` (and gallery if touched)
